  <static seed="110" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/MixedNumberAdditionWordProblems20.pg">
    <statement><p>To pave the road on Ellis Street, the crew used <m>3{{\frac{2}{3}}}</m> tons of cement on the first day, and used <m>1{{\frac{4}{9}}}</m> tons on the second day. How many tons of cement were used in all?</p>
<p><fillin characters="11" name="AnSwEr0001"/> tons of cement were used in all.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>5{\textstyle\frac{1}{9}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>This problem is obviously an addition problem.</p>
<p>To add mixed number, we break each mixed number into an integer and a fraction, and then add up integers and fractions separately.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}[t]
3{{\frac{2}{3}}} + 1{{\frac{4}{9}}} 
      \amp = 3 + {{\frac{2}{3}}} + 1 + {{\frac{4}{9}}} \\
      \amp = 3 + 1 + {{\frac{2}{3}}} + {{\frac{4}{9}}} \\
      \amp = 4 + \frac{2 \cdot 3}{3 \cdot 3} + \frac{4}{9} \\
      \amp = 4 + \frac{6}{9} + \frac{4}{9} \\
      
      \amp = 4 + \frac{10}{9} \\
      \amp = 4 + {1{\textstyle\frac{1}{9}}} \\
      \amp = {5{\textstyle\frac{1}{9}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p><m>{5{\textstyle\frac{1}{9}}}</m> tons of cement were used in all.</p>
</solution>
